args:
Ranzal and Zacharias catch up, and an offer is
made: If Ranzal will return to Saint Lotier, his
father will accept an alliance with New Alberia.
Before he answers, Ranzal departs to the
Davian Wetlands to hunt the fiends there.
The fiends' nest is clear. Now we can—
Wait, Elly. What's that fence over there?
That's the border of the Davian Wetlands.
Place has been sealed off since forever.\nIt's an old battleground littered with\ndangerous ruins.
Even fiends can't get in there.
Now let's hurry up and get back to\nSaint Lotier already.
What is the meaning of this? You claim to\nhave cleared out the nest, yet I've just now\nreceived word we're still beset by fiends!
Hey, that's not OUR fault! We did our job!
But I'm certain there wasn't so much as\na mouse left anywhere around that nest.\nSo where...?
Could they have come from the wetlands?
The place Ranzal said was closed off?
The Davian Wetlands? Impossible.\nA potent ward seals that place.
And yet that's the only remaining\npossibility.
We can't let those fiends have free run of\nSaint Lotier.
We'll go see for ourselves where these\nfiends are coming from. We have to keep\nthe people of the Aquapolis safe!
Ain't no tellin' what'll happen if we enter\nthat forsaken place.
You're going to want to evacuate the north\nside of town, Pops.
Have the city guard issue the order.\nThe sooner the better.
My, my. Look who's learned to think of the\nwelfare of others.
I've only ever known you to worry about\nyour own amusements.
Yeah, well, thousands of innocents dyin'\ndon't strike me as a good time.
Very well, then. Pray continue your hunt.
Your actions have yet to earn my trust as a\npotential ally, but your dedication is noted.
Ranzal, remain with me a moment.
Heh heh. That prince of yours is quite the\nenthusiastic helper.
Though the fact he actually believes his\nefforts might earn him an alliance with\nSaint Lotier is laughable.
Still, he'll be of use—I've a long list of\nerrands he's welcome to complete for me.
Wait, so ya never intended to help?!
But I COULD be convinced to stop using\nhim as my errand boy, if it pleases you.
My terms are quite generous,\nas I think you'll agree.
Come home, Ranzal. Leave that joke of a\nkingdom to flounder on its own and return\nto the city that raised you.
I could even be persuaded to sign an\nalliance with New Alberia if you accept.
And ya'd make an enemy of Dyrenell to\nsee it happen?
I hear tales of Empress Zethia's cruelty on\na daily basis.
She won't ignore Saint Lotier forever.
Perhaps a preemptive strike is our best\nmove—with you at the head of my army.
Think on it. Think on what you—and only\nyou—can do in this situation.
The sons of Saint Lotier are meant to live\nby the sea and with it. So it has always\nbeen, and so it will always be.
That's gotta be where those fiends are\ncoming from.
Um, is something wrong, Ranzal?\nYou haven't said a word since we left.
Er, yeah. Actually, there's somethin' ya\noughta know, {player_name}.
AND he's been lying to us the whole time!
He is SO getting char-grilled when we're\ndone out here.
So what are you going to do?
Not sure. But one thing I AM sure about is\nthat it don't make a bit'a difference what\nya do—he ain't gonna treat ya fair.
Ain't no reason to do this, so we should\nturn back and—
No. Regardless of Zacharias's intentions,\nwe'll go to the wetlands.
It's clear at this point that fiends are\ncoming from inside it.
If we don't deal with them, the people\nof Saint Lotier will continue to suffer.\nThe schemes of their lord are irrelevant.
Heh. You really are a piece of work.
It was like ＂GRRRK KZZZZT!＂ What kind of\nfiend makes a noise like that?
It sounded like no fiend I've ever heard.
It was more like the metal contraptions\nbuilt in the rokkan smithies.
Hate to say I told ya so, but this place is\nseriously bad news.
Let's go. This is just proof we were right.
